# Pipeline Contract (v2)

When changing stages, reruns, flags, or artifacts, review all affected contract files together:

- `src/config.ts` for `stageProfiles`, model defaults, `qualitySettings`, and paths
- `src/types/index.ts` for options, artifact data, statuses, and telemetry
- `src/index.ts` for CLI flags and help text
- `src/blueprint/parse-blueprint.ts` for the Market Promise + Continuity Manifest + Locations sections
- `src/blueprint/compile-author-brief.ts`, `compile-market-promise.ts`, `compile-continuity-manifest.ts`, `compile-locations.ts`
- `src/pipeline/compile-blueprint.ts` for blueprint-level cached artifacts
- `src/pipeline/compile-chapter-packet.ts` for the per-chapter packet contract
- `src/pipeline/generate-spec.ts` for spec-loop sequencing and critique gating
- `src/pipeline/judge-draft.ts` for pass-threshold logic, anti-committee principles, and the bestseller question
- `src/pipeline/revise-draft.ts`, `fix-continuity.ts`, and `apply-revision-patches.ts` for shared `RevisionPlan` / `RevisionDiff` patch contracts
- `src/pipeline/voice-grit-pass.ts` (canonical contract: `docs/voice-grit-spec.md`)
- `src/pipeline/opening-ending-tournament.ts` for the 1-candidate-per-zone opening + ending compare
- `src/pipeline/run-chapter.ts` for orchestration, reuse, and blocking behavior
- `src/pipeline/update-continuity-state.ts` for post-publish state merge
- `src/validators/index.ts` and `src/validators/continuity-manifest.ts`
- `src/pipeline/estimate-cost.ts` when stage names, prompt surfaces, or conditional stage behavior change
- `src/pipeline/stage-utils.ts` for artifact paths/envelopes/status writing
- `README.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `BESTSELLER_ROADMAP.md`, `BLUEPRINT_TEMPLATE.md`, `docs/voice-grit-spec.md`, and relevant `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` when operator-visible behavior or persistent project context changes
- focused tests when runtime behavior changes

Checklist:

- New stage output is persisted as `ArtifactEnvelope<T>`
- Reused artifacts still validate metadata identity (artifactType, blueprintHash, blueprintVersion, chapterNumber)
- Smoke mode still has a deterministic path when practical
- Cost/usage collection stays wired for any new provider call
- `revisionPatch` usage is attributed separately from structural `revision`

Skip-revision artifact contract (CRITICAL):

- When the draft clears `qualitySettings.skipRevisionThreshold` AND has no blocking review signals, revision is skipped.
- The skip path MUST still write `chapter-N-selection.json`, `chapter-N-selected.json`, and `chapter-N-review.json` before voice-grit runs. Rerun-from-judge / rerun-from-memory / audit-only depend on these.
- When revision runs, patch path writes `chapter-N-revised-draft.json` (`ChapterDraft`) plus `chapter-N-revision-diff.json` (`RevisionDiff`); structural rewrite writes only the revised draft.

Single-pipeline invariants (no profile gating):

- Voice-grit runs before the opening/ending tournament so the tournament still owns its reserved zones.
- Voice-grit and tournament are advisory and fail-soft. Either throwing or discarding leaves `selected` unchanged for downstream stages.
- Voice-grit must follow `docs/voice-grit-spec.md`: reserved zones blocked, ticSource validated against `activeTraits` / `dialogueHabits` (for `voice-tic`) or `effectTics.<category>:<entry>` (for `repeated-effect`), taboos excluded for both textures, count caps enforced, atomic whole-batch discard on rejudge regression > 1pt or new blocking review signal.
- Tournament writes `chapter-N-tournament-{opening,ending}.json` zone artifacts (with the final `applied` state) and a merged `chapter-N-tournament-merged.json`.
- Tournament zone artifact must record the final `applied` state before persisting.
- Author brief is one cached model call per blueprint, deterministic-fallback when no credentials or `--no-genre-ai`.
- Voice-target and continuity slice are loaded with soft metadata validation (mismatches return null, never throw).
- Voice-target seeding: `compileBlueprintRuntime` calls `ensureVoiceTargetSeeded` after both cache-hit and cache-miss paths. When `voice-target.json` is absent, it invokes `extractAndPersistVoiceTarget` which falls back to the seed `effectTics` catalog when no published chapters yield ≥200 chars of corpus text. When the file is present, the seed step is a no-op — soft validation in `loadVoiceTargetIfPresent` continues to drop stale-hash artifacts at packet build time.
- Judge POV demographic block: unsourced demographic assertions about non-cast walk-ons (ethnicity, nationality, exact age, training history, professional background, biographical fact) are STRUCTURAL POV violations and MUST enter `blockingIssues` every time. The fix is trivial (observable description, or have a cast character introduce the fact), so the bar for blocking is intentionally low.
- Continuity-fix is patch-only: `chapter-N-fix-attempt-K.json` carries `RevisionDiff`, and validator-only blocking downgrades before the planner runs.
- `TrackedIssue` / `RevisionDiff.issueCoverage` provide per-issue accountability; every issue passed to a patch planner must surface as patched, validation-skipped, planner-skipped, covered by another patch, or unaddressed.
- Continuity-state update is a deterministic post-publish merge that writes `artifacts/blueprint/continuity-state-after-N.json`. It consumes declared spec reveals plus the extracted `ChapterDelta` (reveal/payoff deliveries, persistent-object state changes, irreversible-change notes, and `mistakenBeliefDeltas` per POV character). Chapter `N+1`'s packet builder reads it via `loadPersistedContinuityState`, projects the static slice back to a manifest shape (last-seen bumps, motif progression, delivered reveals), and surfaces `state.mistakenBeliefs` directly as a top-level packet field (NOT through `projectStateToManifest`). Skipped when the blueprint omits a Continuity Manifest. `normalizeChapterDelta` backfills newly-required `ChapterDelta` arrays at every model output, smoke output, and `--rerun-from` artifact load site.

CLI/operator docs stay aligned when flags or runtime stage behavior change.
